tags: dont @ me about tony stark smh
body:
TONY STARK IS IMPORTANT

okay so I’ve encountered someone who thinks Tony Stark deserves to die, and that he’s unimportant. They say hes a “smug playboy that deserves to die.” Or something along those lines. And I’m gonna like,??? Die??? Tony is earths best defender, as they state IN ALMOST EVERY MOVIE TONY STARK IS IN. He isn’t some smug sex induced slut????? He’s actually a nice, sweet man. He’s a AVENGER MIGHT I ADD??? Literally he’s the glue that holds the avengers together. If Tony Stark never existed, or died.

THERE WOULD BE NO AVENGERS??? LIKE ACTUALLY???

so please, stop bullying Tony Stark. I know y’all are out there.

summary: Could you use the sentence starter “I sent you more gifts! Do you like them?” For a reader x tony stark fic?
question: Could you use the sentence starter “I sent you more gifts! Do you like them?” For a reader x tony stark fic?
answer:
Yay more tony!
This is bad please enjoy lol
—————-
Tony was your best friend, a giant dork honestly. He spoiled you so much just as a friend that when he asked you out you had to make a agreement that he won’t spend over 30 dollars on you. While tony was a bit upset he just made a sassy remark and kissed your cheek.
A few months later little gifts turned up at your door step, little plushies that slowly grew in size week by week. You told tony a bunch of gifts were being left at your house, hoping the two of you can find the person, but he didn’t seem to really care. Saying “maybe if they continue to leave them there you can live with me”.
3 days after that there was a giant box, full of so many expensive things. Perfumes, candies, merchandise, gems and jewelry. You just left it there hoping who ever left it would take it back. Next day the door bell rang, not even the afternoon yet. You didn’t bother to answer the door, thinking it’ll just be another gift until the door bell went off again. Tony standing there waiting till you open the door. went you opened the door a smile cover his face “I sent you more gifts! Did you like them?” Excitement hinted in his voice
“Tony.. you were sending them? Wait tony I can’t take all of these things I though I told you that”
“You took them, I thought you would like them?”
“It rained all night I couldn’t let the box get wet-“ you sighed, letting him inside “-can you take all this back? Return it?”
Tony’s face fell a bit “I got everything you liked, why won’t you just accept them?”
“I feel bad, I can’t just have you spend over a hundred dollars on me each day. It doesn’t feel right, tony please.”
Huffing he made a compromise “how about, you start living with me then I’ll stop?”
You sighed and just accepted it, either way it’ll be nice to live with him. Maybe he’ll give you a gift you can’t just buy

summary: For some reason I was looking at what qualities make a good leader and the more I read, the more I felt like I was reading a...
body:
For some reason I was looking at what qualities make a good leader and the more I read, the more I felt like I was reading a description of Tony Stark:

Honesty and integrity, confidence, inspire others (Peter), commitment and passion, good communicator, decision making capabilities (Tony decided immediately to take the spaceship to Titan to fight Thanos on his territory), accountability - “A good leader takes little more than his share of the blame and little less than his share of the credit.” (Tony recognizes that Ultron was entirely his fault), creativity and innovation, empathy, vision, courage, humility.

These are just the first few results I found and I’m not good at developing (plus it seems obvious to me) but feel free to do so if you feel like it haha
